Objective
To create a structured framework for analyzing sales data, identifying trends, and generating actionable insights that can inform business strategies and decision-making processes.

Key Components
Entities
Relationships
Attributes
Processes
1. Entities and Attributes

Sales

Sales_ID: Unique identifier for each sale.
Date: The date the sale occurred.
Product_ID: Identifier for the product sold.
Customer_ID: Identifier for the customer who made the purchase.
Region: Geographic area where the sale took place.
Sales_Amount: Monetary value of the sale.
Quantity_Sold: Number of units sold.
Marketing_Spend_ID: Identifier for the marketing campaign associated with the sale.

Products

Product_ID: Unique identifier for each product.
Product_Name: Name of the product.
Product_Category: Category to which the product belongs.
Price: Sale price of the product.

Customers

Customer_ID: Unique identifier for each customer.
Customer_Name: Name of the customer.
Customer_Segment: Segment classification of the customer (e.g., regular, premium).
Demographics: Information such as age, gender, and location.

Marketing Campaigns

Marketing_Spend_ID: Unique identifier for each marketing campaign.
Campaign_Name: Name of the marketing campaign.
Start_Date: Start date of the campaign.
End_Date: End date of the campaign.
Total_Spend: Total amount spent on the campaign.
Channel: Marketing channel used (e.g., online, in-store).
